About

Growing up I was never really into technology. I always liked being outside playing basketball or playing some type of sports. I was never a gamer, and I didnt own a computer for many years after college. I guess you can say I don't have that typical web development story, of how I've always been into computers. So why am I here?
"You must do the things you think you cannot do." - Eleanor Roosevelt.
Computers have always scared me away because I never really quite understood how it all works. One day while I was hanging out with a good friend of mine, he started working on his project which is a web application for one of his computer science classes. I thought I would see what it was about even though I knew deep down I probably wont understand it. Maybe it was the way he showed me what he was doing and how it all worked, but I started getting pretty intruiged by it. He was showing me how he was able to create things on the page and was able to manipulate them based on specific coding commands. Although "techie" would never be used to describe me before, I usually heard "creative" and "a problem solver" through compliments. What I realized with coding that day is I can improve on those characteristics, and perhaps embark on a journey that I thought I would never take. That night I came home and started watching videos on web development. It did not stop there.
Fast forward to now, after completing some web application projects and finishing a full stack accelerated program with LearningFuze, I have never been more excited to continue learning and improving my coding skills.

  • Operations Analysis

    Building a quality product requires necessary planning and execution. Keeping the user experience in mind at all times, I carefully break down what is needed to be carried out in order to have the most effective way of reaching set goals.

  • Problem Solving

    There is not a better way to stimulate the mind than trying to solve problems. Ever since I can remember, I have always enjoyed playing games such as scavenger hunts and chess which involved a process to finding a solution. Web development not only enables me to continue broadening my way of thinking but also shows me that my potential is endless.

  • Creativity

    What drew me most to web development is that I can express myself in many different ways with it. I think web development is an art, and without art, the world would not be a better place.

  • Time Management

    In a world where everything is always on the go, managing ones time is essential to carrying out the task at hand effectively. I like to set myself up for success by carefully laying out a plan of acion beforehand and by dividing up sections of different task in order to have an organized foundation to successfully execute the work in a timely manner.
